abstract: World Bank head Jim Young Kim says Federal Reserve's decision not to raise interest rates has aided developing countries by giving them time to implement reforms.
lead_paragraph: The head of the World Bank, Jim Yong Kim, said the Federal Reserve’s decision not to raise interest rates gave breathing room to developing countries.

headline.main: Developing Nations Said to Gain From Fed’s Decision on Rates
